<ety>[F. <ets>trou</ets> hole + <ets>de</ets> of + <ets>loup</ets>
wolf.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A pit in the form of an inverted
cone or pyramid, constructed as an obstacle to the approach of an enemy,
and having a pointed stake in the middle. The pits are called also
<altname>trapholes</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
